Logical: InternationalPatientSummary
Title: "International Patient Summary"
Parent: Element
Description: """[openEHR-EHR-COMPOSITION.health_summary.v1] Generic document containing a summary of health information about an individual."""
* ^name = "InternationalPatientSummary"
* ^status = #active
* ^version = "1.0.0-alpha.25"
* ^url = "http://openehr.org/StructureDefinition/InternationalPatientSummary"
* category 1..1 CodeableConcept "category" """[RM] Temporal category of this Composition, persistent / episodic or event."""
* category from InternationalPatientSummaryCategory (required)
* composer 1..1 BackboneElement "composer" """[RM] The person primarily responsible for the content of the Composition (but not necessarily its committal into the EHR system). This is the identifier which should appear on the screen. It may or may not be the person who entered the data. When it is the patient, the special self instance of `PARTY_SELF` will be used."""
* context 1..1 BackboneElement "context" """[RM] `COMPOSITION.context` - Documents the context information of a healthcare event involving the subject of care and the health system. The context information recorded here are independent of the attributes recorded in the version audit, which document the system interaction context, i.e. the context of a user interacting with the health record system. Healthcare events include patient contacts, and any other business activity, such as pathology investigations which take place on behalf of the patient."""
  * startTime 1..1 dateTime "start_time" """[RM] COMPOSITION.context.start_time - Start time of the clinical session or other kind of event during which a provider performs a service of any kind for the patient."""
  * setting 1..1 CodeableConcept "setting" """[RM] The setting in which the clinical session took place. Coded using the openEHR Terminology, setting group."""
  * setting from InternationalPatientSummarySetting (required)
* problemList 0..1 BackboneElement "Problem List" """[openEHR-EHR-SECTION.adhoc.v1] A generic section header which should be renamed in a template to suit a specific clinical context."""
  * ProblemDiagnosis 0..* BackboneElement "Problem/Diagnosis" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis.v1] Details about a single identified health condition, injury, disability or any other issue which impacts on the physical, mental and/or social well-being of an individual."""
    * problemDiagnosisName 1..1 CodeableConcept "Problem/Diagnosis name" """[at0002] Identification of the problem or diagnosis, by name."""
    * bodySite 0..* CodeableConcept "Body site" """[at0012] Identification of a simple body site for the location of the problem or diagnosis."""
    * dateTimeOfOnset 0..1 dateTime "Date/time of onset" """[at0077] Estimated or actual date/time that signs or symptoms of the problem/diagnosis were first observed."""
    * severity 0..1 CodeableConcept "Severity" """[at0005] An assessment of the overall severity of the problem or diagnosis."""
    * severity from InternationalPatientSummarySeverity (preferred)
    * dateOfAbatement 0..1 dateTime "Date of abatement" """[at0030] Estimated or actual date/time of resolution or remission for this problem or diagnosis, as determined by a healthcare professional."""
    * problemDiagnosisQualifier 0..1 BackboneElement "Problem/Diagnosis qualifier" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.problem_qualifier.v2] Contextual or temporal qualifier for a specified problem or diagnosis."""
      * activeInactive 0..1 CodeableConcept "Active/Inactive?" """[at0003] Category that supports division of problems and diagnoses into Active or Inactive problem lists."""
      * activeInactive from InternationalPatientSummaryActiveInactive (required)
      * resolutionPhase 0..1 CodeableConcept "Resolution phase" """[at0083] Phase of healing for an acute problem or diagnosis."""
      * resolutionPhase from InternationalPatientSummaryResolutionPhase (required)
      * remissionStatus 0..1 CodeableConcept "Remission status" """[at0089] Status of the remission of an incurable diagnosis."""
      * remissionStatus from InternationalPatientSummaryRemissionStatus (required)
      * occurrence 0..1 CodeableConcept "Occurrence" """[at0071] Category of the occurrence for this problem or diagnosis."""
      * occurrence from InternationalPatientSummaryOccurrence (required)
    * diagnosticCertainty 0..1 CodeableConcept "Diagnostic certainty" """[at0073] The level of confidence in the identification of the diagnosis."""
    * diagnosticCertainty from InternationalPatientSummaryDiagnosticCertainty (preferred)
    * lastUpdated 0..1 dateTime "Last updated" """[at0070] The date this problem or diagnosis was last updated."""
  * ExclusionGlobal 0..1 BackboneElement "Exclusion - global" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.exclusion_global.v1] An overall statement of exclusion about all Problems/diagnoses, Family history, Medications, Procedures, Adverse reactions or other clinical items that are either not currently present, or have not been present in the past."""
    * globalExclusionOfProblemsDiagnoses 1..1 CodeableConcept "Global exclusion of problems/diagnoses" """[at0002] Overall statement of exclusion of all problems or diagnoses at the time of recording."""
  * AbsenceOfInformation 0..1 BackboneElement "Absence of information" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.absence.v2] Statement that specified health information is not available for inclusion in the health record or extract at the time of recording."""
    * absenceStatement 1..1 CodeableConcept "Absence statement" """[at0002] Positive statement that no information is available."""
    * lastUpdated 0..1 dateTime "Last updated" """[at0004] The date at which the absence was last updated."""
* allergiesAndIntolerances 0..1 BackboneElement "Allergies and Intolerances" """[openEHR-EHR-SECTION.adhoc.v1] A generic section header which should be renamed in a template to suit a specific clinical context."""
  * AllergyIntolerance 0..* BackboneElement "Allergy Intolerance" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.adverse_reaction_risk.v2] Clinical assessment of the propensity for an individual to experience a harmful or undesirable physiological response if exposed, or re-exposed, to a substance."""
    * substance 1..1 CodeableConcept "Substance" """[at0002] Identification of a substance, or substance class, that is considered to put the individual at risk of an adverse reaction event."""
    * verificationStatus 0..1 CodeableConcept "Verification status" """[at0063] Assertion about the certainty of the propensity, or potential future risk, of the identified 'Substance' to cause a reaction."""
    * verificationStatus from InternationalPatientSummaryVerificationStatus (preferred)
    * criticality 0..1 CodeableConcept "Criticality" """[at0101] An indication of the potential for critical system organ damage or life threatening consequence."""
    * criticality from InternationalPatientSummaryCriticality (preferred)
    * type 0..1 CodeableConcept "Type" """[at0058] Identification of the underlying physiological mechanism for the adverse reaction."""
    * reaction 0..* BackboneElement "Reaction" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.adverse_reaction_event.v1] Information about a specific adverse reaction event caused by exposure to a specific substance."""
      * manifestation 1..* CodeableConcept "Manifestation" """[at0006] Clinical symptoms and/or signs that are observed or associated with the adverse reaction."""
      * onset 0..1 dateTime "Onset" """[at0008] The date and/or time of the onset of the reaction."""
      * severity 0..1 CodeableConcept "Severity" """[at0010] Clinical assessment of the severity of the reaction event as a whole, potentially considering multiple different manifestations."""
      * severity from InternationalPatientSummarySeverity2 (preferred)
    * comment 0..1 CodeableConcept "Comment" """[at0006] Additional narrative about the propensity for the adverse reaction, not captured in other fields."""
    * lastUpdated 0..1 dateTime "Last updated" """[at0062] Date when the propensity or the reaction event was updated."""
  * ExclusionGlobal 0..1 BackboneElement "Exclusion - global" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.exclusion_global.v1] An overall statement of exclusion about all Problems/diagnoses, Family history, Medications, Procedures, Adverse reactions or other clinical items that are either not currently present, or have not been present in the past."""
    * globalExclusionOfAdverseReactions 1..1 CodeableConcept "Global exclusion of adverse reactions" """[at0002] Overall statement of exclusion about all adverse reactions at the time of recording."""
  * AbsenceOfInformation 0..1 BackboneElement "Absence of information" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.absence.v2] Statement that specified health information is not available for inclusion in the health record or extract at the time of recording."""
    * absenceStatement 1..1 CodeableConcept "Absence statement" """[at0002] Positive statement that no information is available."""
    * lastUpdated 0..1 dateTime "Last updated" """[at0004] The date at which the absence was last updated."""
* medicationSummary 0..1 BackboneElement "Medication Summary" """[openEHR-EHR-SECTION.adhoc.v1] A generic section header which should be renamed in a template to suit a specific clinical context."""
  * MedicationStatement 0..* BackboneElement "Medication statement" """[openEHR-EHR-ACTION.medication.v1] Any activity related to the planning, scheduling, prescription management, dispensing, administration, cessation and other use of a medication, vaccine, nutritional product or other therapeutic item."""
    * currentState 1..1 CodeableConcept "current_state" """[RM] """
    * currentState from InternationalPatientSummaryCurrentState (required)
    * transition 0..1 CodeableConcept "transition" """[RM] """
    * transition from InternationalPatientSummaryTransition (required)
    * careflowStep 0..1 CodeableConcept "careflow_step" """[RM] `ISM_TRANSITION.care_flow_step` - The step in the careflow process which occurred as part of generating this action, e.g. dispense , start_administration. This attribute represents the clinical label for the activity, as opposed to current_state which represents the state machine (ISM) computable form. Defined in archetype."""
    * careflowStep from InternationalPatientSummaryCareflowStep (required)
    * time 1..1 dateTime "time" """[RM] `ACTION.time` - Point in time at which this action took place."""
    * medicationItem 0..1 CodeableConcept "Medication item" """[at0020] Name of the medication, vaccine or other therapeutic/prescribable item which was the focus of the activity."""
    * medicationDetails 0..1 BackboneElement "Medication details" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.medication.v2] Details about a medication or component of a medication, including strength, form and details of any specific constituents."""
      * name 0..1 CodeableConcept "Name" """[at0132] The name of the medication or medication component."""
      * form 0..* CodeableConcept "Form" """[at0071] The formulation or presentation of the medication or medication component."""
      * category 0..1 CodeableConcept "Category" """[at0142] The category of the medication or medication component, with regard to manufacturing or preparation, and the number of ingredients."""
      * category from InternationalPatientSummaryCategory2 (preferred)
      * strengthPresentation 0..1 BackboneElement "Strength (presentation)" """[at0152] The strength of the medication or medication component, expressed as a ratio."""
        * strengthNumerator 1..1 Quantity "Strength numerator" """[at0153  | ] The numerator of the strength fraction."""
        * strengthDenominator 1..1 Quantity "Strength denominator" """[at0157  | ] The denominator of the strength fraction."""
      * strengthConcentration 0..1 Quantity "Strength (concentration)" """[at0115  | ] The strength of the medication or medication component, as a concentration."""
      * manufacturer 0..1 CodeableConcept "Manufacturer" """[at0151] The manufacturer of the medication or medication component."""
      * batchId[x] 0..* CodeableConcept or Identifier "Batch ID" "at0150: The identifier assigned to the production batch by the manufacturer during production."
      * expiry 0..1 dateTime "Expiry" """[at0003] The expiry date and/or time of the medication or medication component, as given by the manufacturer or individual preparing the mixture."""
      * amount 0..1 Quantity "Amount" """[at0139  | ] The amount of medication or medication component."""
      * alternateAmount 0..1 Quantity "Alternate amount" """[at0148  | ] An equivalent representation of the amount of the medication or medication component."""
      * role 0..1 CodeableConcept "Role" """[at0127] The role of the medication or medication component within a mixture."""
      * role from InternationalPatientSummaryRole (preferred)
      * description 0..1 CodeableConcept "Description" """[at0133] Narrative description of the medication or medication component where it is not possible to describe this fully using structured elements."""
    * dosage 0..1 BackboneElement "Dosage" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.dosage.v2] The combination of a medication amount and administration timing for a single day, in the context of a medication order or medication management."""
      * dose[x] 0..1 Quantity or BackboneElement "Dose" "at0144: The amount of medication administered at one time."
      * doseFormula[x] 0..1 CodeableConcept or Quantity "Dose formula" "at0135: The formula used to calculate the dose amount or administration rate where this is dependent on some other factor, such as body weight or surface area."
      * doseDescription 0..1 CodeableConcept "Dose description" """[at0178] Text description of the dose."""
      * timingDaily 0..1 BackboneElement "Timing - daily" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.timing_daily.v1] Structured information about the intended timing of a therapeutic or diagnostic activity within any 24 hour period."""
        * frequency[x] 0..1 Quantity or BackboneElement "Frequency" "at0003: The frequency as number of times per time period that the activity is to take place."
        * interval 0..1 Duration "Interval" """[at0014] The time interval or minimum and maximum range of an interval between each scheduled activity."""
        * specificTime[x] 0..* time or BackboneElement "Specific time" "at0004: A specific time or interval of time when the activity should occur."
        * timingDescription 0..1 CodeableConcept "Timing description" """[at0027] Text description of the daily timing. This element is intended to allow implementers to use the structures for different timings without necessarily specifying the timings in a structured way."""
        * exactTimingCritical 0..1 boolean "Exact timing critical?" """[at0023] Is exact timing of the activity critical to effectiveness, or patient safety or wellbeing?"""
        * asRequired 0..1 boolean "As required" """[at0024] Record as True if the activity should only occur when the "'As required' criterion" is met."""
        * 'AsRequired'Criterion 0..1 CodeableConcept "'As required' criterion" """[at0025] The condition which triggers an 'As required' activity."""
        * specificEvent 0..* BackboneElement "Specific event" """[at0039] A specific, named time event that the activity should occur in relation to."""
          * eventName 0..1 CodeableConcept "Event name" """[at0026] The name of the event that triggers the activity to take place."""
          * timeOffset 0..1 Duration "Time offset" """[at0040] The period of time before or after the named event when the activity should take place. Negative durations can be used to signify that the activity should take place before the event."""
        * onOffCycle 0..* BackboneElement "On / off cycle" """[at0035] A cycle of activity where an on-off pattern is required."""
          * on 0..1 Duration "On" """[at0036] The period of time for which the activity should take place."""
          * off 0..1 Duration "Off" """[at0037] The period of time for which the activity should NOT take place."""
    * clinicalIndication 0..1 CodeableConcept "Clinical indication" """[at0156] The clinical reason for the medication activity."""
    * administrationDetails 0..1 BackboneElement "Administration details" """[at0140] Details of body site and administration of the medication."""
      * route 0..1 CodeableConcept "Route" """[at0147] The route by which the ordered item was, or is to be, administered into the subject's body."""
      * bodySite 0..1 CodeableConcept "Body site" """[at0141] Structured description of the site of administration of the ordered item."""
    * timingNonDaily 0..1 BackboneElement "Timing - non-daily" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.timing_nondaily.v1] Structured information about the intended timing pattern for a therapeutic or diagnostic activity occurring over days, weeks, months or years."""
      * repetitionInterval 0..1 Duration "Repetition interval" """[at0002] The interval between repetitions of the activity."""
      * daysPerTimePeriod[x] 0..1 Quantity or BackboneElement "Days per time period" "at0014: The number of days per time period on which the activity takes place."
      * activitiesPerTimePeriod[x] 0..1 Quantity or BackboneElement "Activities per time period" "at0022: The number of activities per time period."
      * specificDate[x] 0..* date or BackboneElement "Specific date" "at0001: The activity should take place on a specific date or a specific range of dates."
      * specificDayOfWeek 0..7 CodeableConcept "Specific day of week" """[at0003] The activity should take place on a specific day of the week."""
      * specificDayOfWeek from InternationalPatientSummarySpecificDayOfWeek (required)
      * specificDayOfMonth[x] 0..31 Count or BackboneElement "Specific day of month" "at0004: The activity should take place on a specific day or interval of days of the month."
      * timingDescription 0..1 CodeableConcept "Timing description" """[at0021] Text description of the timing."""
      * specificEvent 0..* BackboneElement "Specific event" """[at0006] The activity should take place in relation to a specific named event."""
        * eventName 0..1 CodeableConcept "Event name" """[at0005] The name of the event that triggers the activity to take place."""
        * timeOffset 0..1 Duration "Time offset" """[at0009] The period of time before or after the named event when the activity should take place. Negative durations can be used to signify that the activity should be taken before a known event."""
      * onOffCycle 0..1 BackboneElement "On / off cycle" """[at0010] A cycle of activity where an on-off pattern is required."""
        * on 0..1 Duration "On" """[at0011] The period of time for which the activity should take place."""
        * off 0..1 Duration "Off" """[at0012] The period of time for which the activity should NOT take place."""
    * orderId[x] 0..* Identifier or CodeableConcept "Order ID" "at0103: Unique identifier for the medication order."
  * ExclusionGlobal 0..1 BackboneElement "Exclusion - global" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.exclusion_global.v1] An overall statement of exclusion about all Problems/diagnoses, Family history, Medications, Procedures, Adverse reactions or other clinical items that are either not currently present, or have not been present in the past."""
    * globalExclusionOfMedicationUse 1..1 CodeableConcept "Global exclusion of medication use" """[at0002] Overall statement of exclusion about the use of all medications at the time of recording."""
  * AbsenceOfInformation 0..1 BackboneElement "Absence of information" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.absence.v2] Statement that specified health information is not available for inclusion in the health record or extract at the time of recording."""
    * absenceStatement 1..1 CodeableConcept "Absence statement" """[at0002] Positive statement that no information is available."""
    * lastUpdated 0..1 dateTime "Last updated" """[at0004] The date at which the absence was last updated."""
* immunizations 0..1 BackboneElement "Immunizations" """[openEHR-EHR-SECTION.adhoc.v1] A generic section header which should be renamed in a template to suit a specific clinical context."""
  * ImmunizationStatement 0..* BackboneElement "Immunization statement" """[openEHR-EHR-ACTION.medication.v1] Any activity related to the planning, scheduling, prescription management, dispensing, administration, cessation and other use of a medication, vaccine, nutritional product or other therapeutic item."""
    * currentState 1..1 CodeableConcept "current_state" """[RM] """
