    * transition from InternationalPatientSummaryTransition2 (required)
    * careflowStep 0..1 CodeableConcept "careflow_step" """[RM] `ISM_TRANSITION.care_flow_step` - The step in the careflow process which occurred as part of generating this action, e.g. dispense , start_administration. This attribute represents the clinical label for the activity, as opposed to current_state which represents the state machine (ISM) computable form. Defined in archetype."""
    * careflowStep from InternationalPatientSummaryCareflowStep2 (required)
    * time 1..1 dateTime "time" """[RM] `ACTION.time` - Point in time at which this action took place."""
    * immunisationItem 0..1 CodeableConcept "Immunisation item" """[at0020] Name of the medication, vaccine or other therapeutic/prescribable item which was the focus of the activity."""
    * clinicalIndication 0..1 CodeableConcept "Clinical indication" """[at0156] The clinical reason for the medication activity."""
    * administrationDetails 0..1 BackboneElement "Administration details" """[at0140] Details of body site and administration of the medication."""
      * route 0..1 CodeableConcept "Route" """[at0147] The route by which the ordered item was, or is to be, administered into the subject's body."""
      * targetSite 0..1 CodeableConcept "Target site" """[at0141] Structured description of the site of administration of the ordered item."""
  * AbsenceOfInformation 0..1 BackboneElement "Absence of information" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.absence.v2] Statement that specified health information is not available for inclusion in the health record or extract at the time of recording."""
    * absenceStatement 1..1 CodeableConcept "Absence statement" """[at0002] Positive statement that no information is available."""
    * lastUpdated 0..1 dateTime "Last updated" """[at0004] The date at which the absence was last updated."""
* diagnosticResults 0..1 BackboneElement "Diagnostic Results" """[openEHR-EHR-SECTION.adhoc.v1] A generic section header which should be renamed in a template to suit a specific clinical context."""
  * LaboratoryTestResult 0..* BackboneElement "Laboratory test result" """[openEHR-EHR-OBSERVATION.laboratory_test_result.v1] The result, including findings and the laboratory's interpretation, of an investigation performed on specimens collected from an individual or related to that individual."""
    * anyEvent 0..* BackboneElement "Any event" """[at0002] Default, unspecified point in time or interval event which may be explicitly defined in a template or at run-time."""
      * testName 1..1 CodeableConcept "Test name" """[at0005] Name of the laboratory investigation performed on the specimen(s)."""
      * specimen 0..1 BackboneElement "Specimen" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.specimen.v1] A physical sample collected from, or related to, an individual for the purpose of investigation, examination or analysis."""
        * specimenType 0..1 CodeableConcept "Specimen type" """[at0029] The type of specimen."""
        * method 0..1 CodeableConcept "Method" """[at0007] The method of collection used."""
        * bodySite 0..1 CodeableConcept "Body site" """[at0087] Identification of the body site or other location from where the specimen is collected."""
      * diagnosticServiceCategory 0..1 CodeableConcept "Diagnostic service category" """[at0077] The diagnostic service or discipline that is responsible for the laboratory test result."""
      * laboratoryAnalyteResult 0..1 BackboneElement "Laboratory analyte result" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.laboratory_test_analyte.v1] The result of a laboratory test for a single analyte value."""
        * analyteName 0..1 CodeableConcept "Analyte name" """[at0024] The name of the analyte result."""
        * analyteResult[x] 0..* CodeableConcept or Attachment or string or State or boolean or Identifier or uri or Duration or Quantity or Count or Ratio or dateTime or time "Analyte result" "at0001: The value of the analyte result."
        * testMethod[x] 0..1 CodeableConcept or Attachment or string or State or boolean or Identifier or uri or Duration or Quantity or Count or Ratio or dateTime or time "Test method" "at0028: Description about the method used to perform the test on this analyte only."
      * interpretation 0..1 CodeableConcept "Interpretation" """[at0057] Narrative description of the key findings."""
      * mediaFile 0..1 BackboneElement "Media file" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.media_file.v1] A media file that is acquired or used as part of the healthcare process, and associated metadata."""
        * content 0..1 Attachment "Content" """[at0001] Digital representation of the media file."""
        * contentName 0..1 CodeableConcept "Content name" """[at0002] Descriptive name or title for the media file."""
      * time 1..1 dateTime "Time" """[RM] `OBSERVATION.EVENT.time` - Time of this Observation event. If the width is non-zero, it is the time point of the trailing edge of the event."""
  * ImagingExaminationResult 0..* BackboneElement "Imaging examination result" """[openEHR-EHR-OBSERVATION.imaging_exam_result.v1] The result of an imaging examination performed on an individual, using radiological techniques."""
    * anyEvent 0..* BackboneElement "Any event" """[at0002] Default, unspecified point in time or interval event which may be explicitly defined in a template or at run-time."""
      * studyName 1..1 CodeableConcept "Study name" """[at0004] The name of the imaging examination performed."""
      * modality 0..* CodeableConcept "Modality" """[at0091] The type of imaging device, process or method that originally acquired or produced the data used to create the images in the study."""
      * targetBodySite 0..1 CodeableConcept "Target body site" """[at0055] Description of the simple body site or region targetted for imaging."""
      * overallResultStatus 0..* CodeableConcept "Overall result status" """[at0072] The status of the imaging examination result as a whole."""
      * overallResultStatus from InternationalPatientSummaryOverallResultStatus (preferred)
      * imagingFindings 0..1 CodeableConcept "Imaging findings" """[at0008] Narrative description or overview of all clinical findings."""
      * imagingExaminationOfABodyStructure 0..1 BackboneElement "Imaging examination of a body structure" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.imaging_exam.v1] Findings on radiological examination of a specified body structure or region."""
        * bodyStructure 1..1 CodeableConcept "Body structure" """[at0001] Identification of the body structure or region examined."""
        * bodySite 0..1 CodeableConcept "Body site" """[at0002] Identification of the area of the body under examination."""
        * imagingFindings 0..1 CodeableConcept "Imaging findings" """[at0004] Narrative description of the imaging findings observed during this examination."""
        * impression 0..* CodeableConcept "Impression" """[at0006] Single word, phrase or brief description that represents the clinical meaning and significance of all imaging findings for the identified body structure."""
        * comment 0..1 CodeableConcept "Comment" """[at0007] Additional narrative about the imaging findings of the body structure, not captured in other fields."""
      * comparisonFindings 0..1 CodeableConcept "Comparison findings" """[at0056] Narrative description about the comparison of this examination with previous similar studies."""
      * imagingQuality 0..1 CodeableConcept "Imaging quality" """[at0063] Assessment about the quality of the examination."""
      * imagingDifferentialDiagnosis 0..* CodeableConcept "Imaging differential diagnosis" """[at0058] Single word, phrase or brief description representing a possible condition or diagnosis."""
      * imagingDiagnosis 0..* CodeableConcept "Imaging diagnosis" """[at0020] Single word, phrase or brief description representing the likely condition or diagnosis."""
      * mediaFile 0..1 BackboneElement "Media file" """[openEHR-EHR-CLUSTER.media_file.v1] A media file that is acquired or used as part of the healthcare process, and associated metadata."""
        * content 0..1 Attachment "Content" """[at0001] Digital representation of the media file."""
        * contentName 0..1 CodeableConcept "Content name" """[at0002] Descriptive name or title for the media file."""
      * time 1..1 dateTime "Time" """[RM] `OBSERVATION.EVENT.time` - Time of this Observation event. If the width is non-zero, it is the time point of the trailing edge of the event."""
    * technique 0..* CodeableConcept "Technique" """[at0087] Name of the radiological procedure used to capture the study."""
    * examinationRequestDetails 0..* BackboneElement "Examination request details" """[at0027] Details about a single imaging examination requested."""
      * receiverOrderIdentifier[x] 0..1 Identifier or CodeableConcept "Receiver order identifier" "at0031: Unique identifier for the imaging examination order assigned by the radiology service."
      * requesterOrderIdentifier[x] 0..1 Identifier or CodeableConcept "Requester order identifier" "at0028: Unique identifier for the imaging examination order assigned by the requester."
      * examinationRequestedName 0..* CodeableConcept "Examination requested name" """[at0029] Identification of imaging examination requested."""
* advanceDirectives 0..1 BackboneElement "Advance Directives" """[openEHR-EHR-SECTION.adhoc.v1] A generic section header which should be renamed in a template to suit a specific clinical context."""
  * AdvanceCareDirective 0..* BackboneElement "Advance care directive" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.advance_care_directive.v2] A framework to communicate the preferences of an individual for future medical treatment and care."""
    * typeOfDirective 0..1 CodeableConcept "Type of directive" """[at0005] The type of advance care directive."""
    * status 0..1 CodeableConcept "Status" """[at0004] The status of the advance care directive."""
    * status from InternationalPatientSummaryStatus (preferred)
    * description 0..1 CodeableConcept "Description" """[at0006] Narrative description of the overall advance care directive."""
    * condition 0..* CodeableConcept "Condition" """[at0007] The conditions or situations in which the individual wishes the advance care directive to apply."""
    * comment 0..1 CodeableConcept "Comment" """[at0038] Additional narrative about the advance care directive not captured in other fields."""
    * validPeriodStart 0..1 dateTime "Valid period start" """[at0053] The date/time that marks the beginning of the valid period of time for this advance care directive."""
    * validPeriodEnd 0..1 dateTime "Valid period end" """[at0054] The date/time that marks the conclusion of the valid period of time for this advance care directive."""
    * reviewDueDate 0..1 dateTime "Review due date" """[at0056] The date at which the advance care directive is due to be reviewed."""
    * lastUpdated 0..1 dateTime "Last updated" """[at0055] The date when this advance directive record was last updated."""
    * mandate[x] 0..* CodeableConcept or uri "Mandate" "at0027: Description of any legislation or other authoritative guidance that apply."
    * directiveLocation 0..* BackboneElement "Directive location" """[at0058] Information about the physical or digital location of the Advance care directive."""
      * location[x] 0..1 CodeableConcept or uri "Location" "at0030: Physical or digital location of the Advance care directive."
  * AdvanceInterventionDecisions 0..1 BackboneElement "Advance intervention decisions" """[openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.advance_intervention_decisions.v1] Anticipatory decisions about the overall intent of care and possible interventions (including treatments, activities, and diagnostic or therapeutic procedures), asserted by a clinician."""
